ry concerns—public and private space, sustainability, ethnic and racial divisions, and technology—this volume illuminates how global society has imagined American urban life.Contributors: Klaus Benesch, Dolores Hayden, David M. Lubin, Malcolm McCullough, Jeffrey L. Meikle, David E. Nye, Miles Orvell, Andrew Ross, Mabel O. Wilson, Albena Yaneva.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecture and societyzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aCities and townszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aCity planningzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 4aArchitecture. 7aARCHITECTURE / Buildings / Public, Commercial & Industrial.2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aArchitecture.  aTechnology and Engineering.  aUrban Studies.1 aBenesch, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenesch, Klaus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHayden, Dolores, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayden, Dolores.1 aLubin, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCullough, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeikle, Jeffrey L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNye, David E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrvell, Miles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrvell, Miles, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoss, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Mabel O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYaneva, Albena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBo